peopleAlsoAsk.question: Are 1945 quarters rare?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: The 1945 is the fifth lowest mintage of the 1932 to 1964 Philadelphia Mint Washingon quarters after the 1932, 1938, 1949, and 1958. It is a little bit tougher to find in Gem MS65 condition and a lot tougher to find in Superb Gem MS66 condition than the other P-Mints of the era.
